,
as Tzitzis reentered her chamber.
`Elic.'
`He is a good messenger.'
`He is a jealous one.'
`Thou forgetest this youth's destiny?' said the princess, reprovingly.
`But Elic knoweth it not, and went with reluctance. He accused me of
desiring to see him.'
`He will soon be undeceived, Tzitzis,' said the princess, smiling; `so do
